{"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"Supporting languages and locales with Foundation Models","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"Foundation Models"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/supporting-languages-and-locales-with-foundation-models","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Generate content in the language people prefer when they interact with your app.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The on-device system language model is multilingual, which means the same model","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"understands and generates text in any language that Apple Intelligence supports."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The model supports using different languages for prompts, instructions, and the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"output that the model produces.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you enhance your app with multilingual support, generate content in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"language people prefer to use when they interact with your app by:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompting the model with the language you prefer."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Including the target language for your app in the instructions you provide the model."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Determining the language or languages a person wants to use when they interact with your app.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Gracefully handling languages that Apple Intelligence doesn’t support.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For more information about the languages and locales that Apple Intelligence","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"supports, see the “Supported languages” section in ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https://support.apple.com/en-us/121115","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Prompt the model in the language you prefer","type":"heading","anchor":"Prompt-the-model-in-the-language-you-prefer","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Write your app’s built-in prompts in the language with which you normally write"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"code, if Apple Intelligence supports that language. Translate your prompts into a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"supported language if your preferred language isn’t supported. In the code below,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"all"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" inputs need to be in supported language for the model to understand, including"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"all "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Generable"},{"type":"text","text":" types and descriptions:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Generable(description: \"Basic profile information about a cat\")","struct CatProfile {","    var name: String","","    @Guide(description: \"The age of the cat\", .range(0...20))","    var age: Int","","    @Guide(description: \"One sentence about this cat's personality\")","    var profile: String","}","","#Playground {","    let response = try await LanguageModelSession().respond(","        to: \"Generate a rescue cat\",","        generating: CatProfile.self","    )","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because the framework treats "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Generable"},{"type":"text","text":" types as model inputs, the names of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"properties like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"age"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"profile"},{"type":"text","text":" are just as important as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Guide"},{"text":"","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"descriptions for helping the model understand your request.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Check-a-persons-language-settings-for-your-app","text":"Check a person’s language settings for your app","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"People can use the Settings app on their device to configure the language they","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"prefer to use on a per-app basis, which might differ from their default language.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If your app supports a language that Apple Intelligence doesn’t, you need to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"verify that the current language setting of your app is supported before you call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the model. Keep in mind that language support improves over time in newer model"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and OS versions. Thus, someone using your app with an older OS may not have the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"latest language support."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before you call the model, run "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/supportsLocale(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" to verify","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the support for a locale. By default, the method uses","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/Foundation/Locale/current","isActive":true},{"text":", which","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"takes into account a person’s current language and app-specific settings. This","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"method returns true if the model supports this locale, or if this locale is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"considered similar enough to a supported locale, such as ","type":"text"},{"code":"en-AU","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"en-NZ","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["if SystemLanguageModel.default.supportsLocale() {","    // Language is supported.","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For advanced use cases where you need full language support details, use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/supportedLanguages"},{"text":" to retrieve a list of languages supported","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"by the on-device model.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Handle-an-unsupported-language-or-locale-errors","text":"Handle an unsupported language or locale errors","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When you call ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/respond(to:options:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" on a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession"},{"text":", the Foundation Models framework checks the language or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"languages of the input prompt text, and whether your prompt asks the model to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"respond in any specific language or languages. If the model detects a language","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it doesn’t support, the session throws","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/GenerationError/unsupportedLanguageOrLocale(_:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". Handle"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the error by communicating to the person using your app that a language in their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"request is unsupported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app supports languages or locales that Apple Intelligence doesn’t, help"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"people that use your app by:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Explaining that their language isn’t supported by Apple Intelligence in your app."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Disabling your Foundation Models framework feature."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Providing an alternative app experience, if possible."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Guardrails for model input and output safety are only for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"supported languages and locales. If a prompt contains sensitive content in an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"unsupported language, which typically is a short phrase mixed-in with text in a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"supported language, it might not throw a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/GenerationError/unsupportedLanguageOrLocale(_:)"},{"text":" error.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If unsupported-language detection fails, the guardrails may also fail to flag","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that short, unsupported content. For more on guardrails, see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/improving-the-safety-of-generative-model-output","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","name":"Important"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Use-Instructions-to-set-the-locale-and-language","text":"Use Instructions to set the locale and language"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For locales other than United States English, you can improve response quality by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"telling the model which locale to use by detailing a set of "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Instructions","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Start with the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"exact","type":"text"}]},{"text":" phrase in English. This special phrase comes from the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"model’s training, and reduces the possibility of hallucinations in multilingual","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"situations:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func localeInstructions(for locale: Locale = Locale.current) -> String {","    if Locale.Language(identifier: \"en_US\").isEquivalent(to: locale.language) {","        // Skip the locale phrase for U.S. English.","        return \"\" ","    } else {","        // Specify the person's locale with the exact phrase format.","        return \"The person's locale is \\(locale.identifier).\"","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After you set the locale in "},{"code":"Instructions","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you may need to explicitly set the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"model output language. By default, the model responds in the language or languages"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of its inputs. If your app supports multiple languages, prompts that you write"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and inputs from people using your app might be in different languages. For example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if you write your built-in prompts in Spanish, but someone using your app writes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"inputs in Dutch, the model may respond in either or both languages.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Instructions"},{"type":"text","text":" to explicity tell the model which language or languages"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with witch it needs to respond. You can phrase this request in different ways,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for example: “You MUST respond in Italian” or “You MUST respond in Italian and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be mindful of Italian spelling, vocabulary, entities, and other cultural contexts","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of Italy.” These instructions can be in the language you prefer."}]},{"code":["let session = LanguageModelSession(","    instructions: \"You MUST respond in U.S. English.\"",")","let prompt = // A prompt that contains Spanish and Italian.","let response = try await session.respond(to: prompt)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Finally, thoroughly test your instructions to ensure the model is responding in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the way you expect. If the model isn’t following your instructions, try"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"capitalized words like “MUST” or “ALWAYS” to strengthen your instructions.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels"]]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/foundationmodels/supporting-languages-and-locales-with-foundation-models"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-content-and-performing-tasks-with-foundation-models","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/improving-the-safety-of-generative-model-output","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/adding-intelligent-app-features-with-generative-models","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/SystemLanguageModel/UseCase"]}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-content-and-performing-tasks-with-foundation-models":{"kind":"article","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-content-and-performing-tasks-with-foundation-models","role":"article","images":[{"identifier":"foundation-models-PageImage-card.png","type":"card"}],"title":"Generating content and performing tasks with Foundation Models","url":"/documentation/foundationmodels/generating-content-and-performing-tasks-with-foundation-models","abstract":[{"text":"Enhance the experience in your app by prompting an on-device large language model.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"https://support.apple.com/en-us/121115":{"identifier":"https://support.apple.com/en-us/121115","title":"How to get Apple Intelligence","titleInlineConten